events.body:
@jonasschnelli can you please check out my updated PR?

I really don't think we need `INVALID_ADDRESS` _and_ `INVALID_PARAMETER`; addresses are request parameters after all. Since a lot of the `INVALID_ADDRESS` were basically meaning "address not found" I changed the error code for the validity checks to `INVALID_PARAMETER`, so `INVALID ADDRESS` can be cleanly renamed to `NOT_FOUND` with a broader use case (such as looking up blocks that doesn't exist).

Regards,

